        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indonesia/12–2448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Baruch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-24T23:00:00+01:00">December 24, 1948—11 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>907. Boon, Foreign Office, indicated to Embassy officer tonight that <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> action was not “unsatisfactory” to Netherlands
                    and that Netherlands Government would be as conciliatory as possible in its
                    reaction to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> resolution. He said Netherlands
                    would probably reply to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> on Monday, December
                    27, by which time he thought military action as such would be completed. Boon,
                    who was obviously relieved by <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> action in
                    eliminating withdrawal clause, was nonetheless at pains to emphasize Netherlands
                    serious concern about sharpness world reaction.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 907, repeated Paris 101 for Jessup.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baruch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
